---
name: std-ui-i18n
backends: [int]
---

# cross-module reactive i18n — computedSignal over an imported module's val, read via sig()
#
# INT-scoped: this guards the interpreter closure-capture + signal-read fix that makes a
# `computedSignal(() => … moduleVal …)` thunk in an imported module resolve cross-interpreter.
# The JS/JVM backends lower closures lexically and never had this bug; their reactive `sig()`
# semantics and opaque-type imports run through the SPA emit path, not the emit-js lane.

[greetingSignal, activeLocale](../../examples/std-ui/i18n-cap-lib.ssc)

```scalascript
val g = greetingSignal()
println(g())
println(activeLocale())
```
